<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[144,1105,1046,1439]" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">
This species is known from numerous sites, all in Stellenbosch district, Western Cape. Described from an unknown locality by Rosa (1891), reported by Michaelsen (1913 
<emphasis box="[1083,1097,1222,1246]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">a</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[144,158,1254,1278]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">b</emphasis>
) and Pickford (1975) from garden soil in Stellenbosch. Two recently collected adult specimens (NMSA/Olig.03925), and verbal information from Frana Fourie (University of Stellenbosch), confirm a large population of this species near a local dam in Papegaaiberg close to Stellenbosch. It is noteworthy that 
<taxonomicName box="[788,884,1350,1374]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Microchaetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="benhami">
<emphasis box="[788,884,1350,1374]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">benhami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Plisko 1992" authorityName="Plisko" authorityYear="1992" box="[236,462,1382,1407]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Microchaetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mkuzi">
<emphasis box="[236,301,1382,1406]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">mkuzi</emphasis>
(Plisko 1992)
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in natural sites in northern KwaZulu-Natal (Plisko 1992, 1998, 2003).
</paragraph>
